Re: Director Real Estate - Technology Position

As a knowledgeable and skilled Director of IT Projects, I can offer the hiring company a unique blend of talent, commitment, and experience. I have attached my resume for your review in regards to the Director Read Estate Technology position.

The work I have performed in previous positions serves as building blocks for future career growth. I enjoy facing challenges and see them as opportunities to make a significant contribution to any organization. I can provide the company with the skills and abilities to positively impact the future success of the organization.

My qualifications include:
* Development and implementation of IT methodologies for change control, project management, and software testing
* Global software implementation and management successes
* Management of large to small diverse groups of stakeholders in matrix and traditional organizations

Thank you in advance for your time and consideration, I look forward to setting up an interview at your convenience to discuss this opportunity further. I would like to direct you to a section of my resume where I was a consultant working at CTI in Dallas, TX. In this position, I participated in the development of a property management system for Cadllac Fairview in Canada.

Thank you.


Sincerely,

Positions.Description:
As a Managing Key Contributor of this IT consulting company, participated in the recommendation and implementation of company direction and policy. Developed the company's change control methodology used at all of DTI's JDEdwards World customers, bringing a substantial savings and structure in change management to our customers and providing a selling tool for DTI.
Successfully managed many of the large multi-year, global projects that DTI won. Globally implemented JDEdwards OneWorld and World applications for many industries inclusive of health care, petrochemicals, consumer products, manufacturing, distribution, and retail.
Adept at managing multi-faceted teams to attain the customer's goals at the same time attaining DTI's goals of supplying excellent project execution and bottom line results. Provided processes and structures for change control methodologies at a number of large global installations.
Opened the Rutherford, New Jersey branch office.

Baxter International:
Managed a large combined staff in a multi-year implementation of a 24 computer, global database with an update and use methodology in Baxter's JDEdwards World and OneWorld applications; enabling Baxter to improve communication between branches, improve supply chain, and have usable, easy global reporting.
Chevron Chemicals:
Managed a large technical team on a multiple year and phase project from inception to implementation of Chevron's JDEdwards World and OneWorld software along with a number of secondary applications.
Gateway:
Furnished the expertise required to develop the structure and method of change control over Gateway's multi-computered environment. Provided the technical expertise necessary to develop the method of combining terabytes of JDEdwards data contained in databases worldwide.
Quaker Chemical Corporation:
Set business process direction for a global implementation of JDEdwards order to cash processes in OneWorld.
Bic Corporation:
Managed a large and diverse staff in a JDEdwards OneWorld coexistent implementation. Laid down processes to control software development, change control, and implementations.
Williams-Sonoma:
Managed the design and implementation of a new order entry system for catalog sales. The new system enabled Williams-Sonoma's customer service agents to better serve their customers through greater merchandise knowledge and speed of supplying answers.
